{"ts":"2026-07-05T05:09:13.638Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-je50"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"Promote plan workflow primitives to the public SDK: plan create/steps/dependencies/decisions/discoveries/validation/materialization"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"pm plan implements durable agent planning workflows (Codex/Claude/Cursor-style: steps with status transitions, dependencies, decisions, discoveries, validation results, materialization into tracked items) but its orchestration lives CLI-side and is not covered by any existing promotion item. SDK-first plus the universal-tool story (pm-w89s) require plan primitives to be public typed API so agent harnesses, MCP pm_plan, and custom tools consume the same engine. Duplicate check: pm-v7dj (closed original plan feature), pm-z5nb (open Plan item about the schema epic, unrelated); no open SDK-promotion overlap."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Feature"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["architecture","area:plan","area:sdk"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-05T05:09:13.638Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-05T05:09:13.638Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/estimated_minutes","value":240},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"SDK exports typed plan primitives covering the full pm plan surface (create with stepTitle, step lifecycle, dependencies, decisions, discoveries, validation, materialize) with identical governance and history semantics; CLI and MCP plan surfaces consume only these primitives; docstrings + linked tests + SDK reference docs; zero behavior change (plan specs green)."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-usfg"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"medium"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":"medium"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/dependencies","value":[{"id":"pm-lodl","kind":"blocked_by","created_at":"2026-07-05T05:09:13.638Z"},{"id":"pm-muhw","kind":"blocked_by","created_at":"2026-07-05T05:09:13.638Z"}]}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"91a71c7cd364de2dc0219199d02522cb73a5e24188e38fefbb78e26608a28630","message":""}
{"ts":"2026-07-10T21:30:53.591Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"note_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-10T21:30:53.591Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/notes","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-10T21:30:53.590Z","author":"maintainer-agent","text":"Implementation slicing 2026-07-10 (grounded in current src state). Already public — do NOT redo: the pm_plan MCP surface and generic plan action dispatch; profile *planning* (planProfileApplication from core/profile/profile-plan.ts) is a different domain and already exported. The actual gap: the ENTIRE plan workflow lives in src/cli/commands/plan.ts (1,796 lines) — there is no src/core/plan module at all, making this the largest single-module promotion left in the epic besides test.ts. Plan is also the agent-harness surface (Codex/Claude/Cursor-style planning), so primitive-level promotion is what makes SDK-embedded planning harnesses possible without shelling out. Suggested slices: S1 plan document model + step lifecycle primitives (~90m) — create with stepTitle, step transitions, plan read model. S2 plan annotation primitives (~60m) — dependencies/decisions/discoveries; shapes should mirror the pm-zwpp S1 annotation kernel — coordinate so plan does not grow a second annotation engine. S3 validation + materialization primitives (~60m) — materialize creates real items and MUST consume the shipped lifecycle primitives (pm-98cz) rather than private paths; this is the primitive-level fix site for pm-qd2h / GH-452 (materialize dead-ends on required-on-create custom fields) and pm-ypha / GH-453 (materialize --json omits title/type/parent) — coordinate with both, do not duplicate their fixes. S4 typed PmClient facades + SDK reference docs/tests (~30m), result shapes matching runAction oracle. Order: strictly S1 -> S2 -> S3 -> S4 (each layer consumes the previous one)."}]}],"before_hash":"91a71c7cd364de2dc0219199d02522cb73a5e24188e38fefbb78e26608a28630","after_hash":"ec02a9eb96d98f79c3dd0be91de639ec72fae7b42f1c6861a369eec0b712a4e8"}
